TWEAK_QUICK_TOOLKIT_TOOLTIP_WINDOW_STYLE				espen

	Sets the window style to use for tooltips

	The value must be a defined OpWindow style. Some configurations
	can not use the default style. OpWindow::STYLE_TOOLTIP is an alternative

	Category			: setting
	Define				: TOOLTIP_WINDOW_STYLE
	Value				: OpWindow::STYLE_POPUP
	Value for desktop	: OpWindow::STYLE_POPUP
	Depends on			: nothing

TWEAK_QUICK_TOOLKIT_SELECTABLE_FILLS_BY_DEFAULT			wdzierzanowski

	Whether selectables fill horizontally by default

	If turned on, "selectable" widgets (check-boxes, radio buttons) will
	expand horizontally to fill the space available in the container.  If they
	are stacked horizontally, this will have the effect of making the entire
	row occupied by a selectable clickable rather than just the box/radio and
	the text.

	Category		: settings
	Define			: QUICK_TOOLKIT_SELECTABLE_FILLS_BY_DEFAULT
	Depends on		: nothing
	Enabled for		: desktop

